<h1>Difference from mean elevation</h1>

<p>This tool can be used to calculate the difference in between the elevation of each grid cell in an input DEM and the average elevation in the local neighbourhood. The local neighbourhood is defined as a circular area of a user-specified dimension surrounding each grid cell. <p>Grid cells containing <b><i>NoData</i></b> values in any of the input images are assigned the <b><i>NoData</i></b> value in the output raster. The output raster is of the <i>float</i> data type and <i>continuous</i> data scale.</p>

<br>

